column4: Vegan burger company Beyond Meat's IPO sizzles with $25 share price
column5: Vegan burger maker Beyond Meat Inc  which counts Microsoft founder Bill Gates and actor Leonardo DiCaprio among its investors  on Wednesday priced its initial public stock offering at $25 per share  the top of its anticipated range in a reflection of brisk investor demand. | Video

column4: UPDATE 1-Vegan burger company Beyond Meat's IPO sizzles with $25 share price
column5: May 1 Vegan burger maker Beyond Meat Inc  which counts Microsoft founder Bill Gates and actor Leonardo DiCaprio among its investors  on Wednesday priced its initial public stock offering at $25 per share  the top of its anticipated range in a reflection of brisk investor demand.

column4: Tesla ends 'Spartan diet' and seeks $2.3 billion to fund expansion
column5: Tesla Inc will raise up to $2.3 billion in new capital  renouncing what Elon Musk called a "Spartan diet" and easing Wall Street concerns about the money-losing company's ability to overcome a drop in sales and build new product lines. | Video

column4: UPDATE 7-Tesla ends 'Spartan diet' and seeks $2.3 bln to fund expansion
column5: May 2 Tesla Inc will raise up to $2.3 billion in new capital  renouncing what Elon Musk called a "Spartan diet" and easing Wall Street concerns about the money-losing company's ability to overcome a drop in sales and build new product lines.

column4: Exclusive: U.S. seeks to challenge China's electric-vehicle supply chain dominance
column5: WASHINGTON A U.S. senator plans to introduce legislation on Thursday to streamline regulation and permitting requirements for the development of mines for lithium  graphite and other electric-vehicle supply chain minerals  part of a plan to offset China's dominance in the space.

column4: Exclusive: Tesla expects global shortage of electric vehicle battery minerals - sources
column5: WASHINGTON Tesla Inc expects global shortages of nickel  copper and other electric-vehicle battery minerals down the road due to underinvestment in the mining sector  the company's global supply manager for battery metals told an industry conference on Thursday  according to two sources.

column4: Tesla to reduce solar panel prices by up to 16%: NYT
column5: (This April 30 NYT story corrects the difference in price between the Tesla panels and the national average to 16 percent from 38 percent)

column4: CORRECTED-OFFICIAL-UPDATE 1-Tesla to reduce solar panel prices by up to 16 pct - NYT
column5: April 30 Tesla Inc plans to announce on Tuesday that it has started selling solar panels and related equipment for up to 16 percent below the national average price  the New York Times reported on Tuesday.

column4: Tesla files for offering to raise capital
column5: May 2 Tesla Inc filed for a mixed shelf offering for an undisclosed amount on Thursday  a week after Chief Executive Officer Elon Musk suggested a capital raise could be imminent.

column4: Wesfarmers bets on electric cars with $544 million bid for Australian lithium miner Kidman
column5: SYDNEY/MELBOURNE Australian retail conglomerate Wesfarmers Ltd offered A$776 million ($544 million) to buy lithium miner Kidman Resources Ltd on Thursday  its second bid in two months to deepen its exposure to high-tech minerals.
